1 While thus along the brink, one before the other,
2 we went our way, and often the good master
3 said to me: "Look: it is good that I make you shrewd";

4 the sun was striking me on my right shoulder,
5 which already, with its rays, was changing all the west
6 from a white appearance to a light blue;

